The paper deals with macroscopic traffic models, which involve optimization and control of traffic flow in road networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Robotics (cs.RO), and Control Systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the optimization problem and constraints involved in traffic flow, which could place it in the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper proposes a solution algorithm that involves tuning parameters, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
